Question: Many universities require that freshman live on campus dorm during the first year of college. In your opinion, is this a good or a bad thing? Explain your opinion on this issue.
Answer:
I believe that such requirement has more benefits over drawbacks. It is true this requirement may limit options of lifestyle for some freshmen, even at the expenses of higher budgets. Nevertheless, it is an effective way to get involved with new campus by interacting with hallmates and joining group events on a frequent base.  Furthermore, living on campus can save time from communion. In sum,  this requirement helps freshmen to adopt to college life, which is essential for college success.